	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've converted tepples' PNG to CHR data (a single 4K page), as well as took my own stab at it.<br /><br />The mapping for my version:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">il digraph: &lt; ($3C)<br />ll digraph: = ($3D)<br />cursor: &gt; ($3E), as in the original table<br />©: @ ($40)<br />←: &#91; ($5B)<br />li digraph: ($5C)<br />→: &#93; ($5D)<br />…: _ ($5F)<br />“: ` ($60)<br />↑: { ($7B)<br />l' digraph: | ($7C)<br />↓: } ($7D)<br />•: ~ ($7E)<br /></div><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">bootmii wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">the [font] on my computer has been wiped out due to an all-$F palette somehow becoming the default in YY-CHR</div><br />Sounds like you might need to replace yychr.pal and yychr.dat from the original files. Hopefully that will fix it.

		
